content: Presidential election in Singapore Indirect Presidential elections were held in [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore) on 31 August 1989. During the election, 69 members of Parliament were present and 13 members were absent. [Wee Kim Wee](/wiki/Wee_Kim_Wee) was re-elected by the [Parliament of Singapore](/wiki/Parliament_of_Singapore).
